<div id="review_3372396230" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372396230" />
    <a title="emma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32879029-emma"><img alt="emma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1520568130p2/32879029.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3372396230?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="emma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="emma" href="/user/show/32879029-emma">emma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32879029-emma?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32879029-emma?shelf=3-and-a-half-stars">3-and-a-half-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32879029-emma?shelf=owned">owned</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32879029-emma?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32879029-emma?shelf=diverse">diverse</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32879029-emma?shelf=non-ya">non-ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32879029-emma?shelf=authors-of-color">authors-of-color</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3372396230" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16469701026295238310">If somehow you have made it to July 2020 without being convinced that we need to burn the entire American justice system down and try again - go ahead and give this book a try.<br/><br/>Come back when you’re finished.<br/><br/>Okay, now that we’re all on the same page, literally and figuratively:<br/><br/>This book is so f*cking hard to read. It’s painful. It’s hard to like any of these characters, or dislike them, for that matter.<br/><br/>They are right and wrong and hurting and hurt and overall so goddamn human. It kills.<br/><br/>This story</span>
  <span id="freeText16469701026295238310" style="display:none">If somehow you have made it to July 2020 without being convinced that we need to burn the entire American justice system down and try again - go ahead and give this book a try.<br /><br />Come back when you’re finished.<br /><br />Okay, now that we’re all on the same page, literally and figuratively:<br /><br />This book is so f*cking hard to read. It’s painful. It’s hard to like any of these characters, or dislike them, for that matter.<br /><br />They are right and wrong and hurting and hurt and overall so goddamn human. It kills.<br /><br />This story is a necessary reminder that when we call innocent people guilty they are branded with the consequences of that guilt.<br /><br />When our justice system messes up, it messes up forever.<br /><br />And it disproportionately destroys the lives of Black Americans.<br /><br />Black people are disproportionately wrongfully convicted, disproportionately executed for crimes, disproportionately kept in prison and for longer sentences and for lesser crimes. <br /><br />If you are a fiction lover above all else, read this book, if it’ll help drive any of that home. <br /><br />And then read Just Mercy. Read nonfiction as well as fiction. Donate and march. If you are white, use your privilege for good, for once.<br /><br />This needs to end.<br /><br />Bottom line: We should aspire to live in a country where stories like this one are just that. Fiction.<br /><br />------------<br /><i>pre-review</i><br /><br />if you're in the market for a reminder that life is complicated and imperfect and there's no such thing as "the right thing" and we are doomed to hurt everyone we love...<br /><br />may i recommend this book?<br /><br />review to come / 3.5 stars<br /><br />------------<br /><br />reading this book about a man falsely imprisoned for a crime he didn't commit as part of my "Burn Down the American Justice System and Try Again" series<br /><br />---<br /><br /><i>i am spending this month reading books by Black authors. please join me!</i><br /><br />book 1: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2953004100?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Stars and the Blackness Between Them</a><br />book 2: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372388250?type=review#rating_290994509" rel="nofollow noopener">Homegoing</a><br />book 3: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2718387154?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Let's Talk about Love</a><br />book 4: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3090142486?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Why I'm No Longer Talking to White People about Race</a><br />book 5: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3227618881?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Sellout</a><br />book 6: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372395187?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Queenie</a><br />book 7: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372400231?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">Red at the Bone</a><br />book 8: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2586355320?book_show_action=false" rel="nofollow noopener">The Weight of the Stars</a><br />book 9: An American Marriage</span>
  <a data-text-id="16469701026295238310" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

